{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TBGhNBQ33rT2xYcvv32yzQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate exactly 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files for testing. Let me analyze the requirements:\n\n1. Save to: `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.21.txt`\n2. Filename rules:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match main title in content (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. Recipe mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n4. Variety of categories and title lengths\n\n5. AVOID these existing recipes (they provided a long list)\n\n6. PATTERN REQUIREMENTS:\n   - 5 files with OCR_CORRUPTION (misrecognized characters, hyphenation artifacts, garbage tokens)\n   - 3 files with NARRATIVE (prose intro 3-7 lines between title and ingredients)\n   - 2 files with COMPOUND (multiple recipes in one title)\n\n7. File length: 15-60 lines, spillover files should be longer\n\nLet me plan the 10 files:\n- 5 files with OCR corruption\n- 3 files with narrative\n- 2 files with compound titles\n\nI need to make sure:\n- ~60% English, ~40% Polish (so roughly 6 English, 4 Polish)\n- All different from the excluded list\n- Mix of categories and title lengths\n\nLet me create:\n\n1. **OCR CORRUPTION - English**: \"Roasted Garlic and Herb Salmon\" - English, OCR corrupted\n2. **OCR CORRUPTION - Polish**: \"Łazanki ze Smietaną\" - Polish, OCR corrupted\n3. **OCR CORRUPTION - English**: \"Beet and Walnut Salad\" - English, OCR corrupted\n4. **OCR CORRUPTION - English**: \"Mushroom Crepe Appetizer\" - English, OCR corrupted\n\n\n5. **OCR CORRUPTION - Polish**: \"Zupa z Dyni i Imbiru\" - Polish, OCR corrupted\n\n6. **NARRATIVE - English**: \"Apple Cinnamon Cake\" - English with narrative intro\n7. **NARRATIVE - Polish**: \"Piernik z Czarnuszką\" - Polish with narrative intro\n8. **NARRATIVE - English**: \"Baked Cod with Lemon\" - English with narrative intro\n\n9. **COMPOUND - English**: \"Focaccia with Rosemary and Focaccia with Olives\" - English compound recipe\n10. **COMPOUND - Polish**: \"Żurawina Kompot i Żurawina Dżem\" - Polish compound recipe\n\nNow checking each against the exclusion list to ensure none match. Roasted Garlic and Herb Salmon, Łazanki ze Smietaną, Beet and Walnut Salad, Mushroom Crepe Appetizer, Zupa z Dyni i Imbiru, Apple Cinnamon Cake, Piernik z Czarnuszką, Baked Cod with Lemon, and the focaccia and żurawina combinations all clear—none appear in the restricted items.\n\nThe distribution looks right: six English dishes, four Polish ones, totaling ten. The breakdown across file types also checks out—five OCR corruptions, three narrative pieces, and two compound entries. Now I need to create realistic OCR text for each, incorporating ingredients and measurements, with character substitutions and hyphenation errors for the corrupted files, and narrative-style descriptions for the others. arlıc, herbs ın bowl UuIw\n3. Pat salmon dry ano place on baking sheet\n4. Spread herb-batter over fillets\n5. Roast for 12-15 minuto\n6. Garnish with lemon sices ano fresh thyme\n\nThe filenames need to match the titles exactly in title case format, following the pattern shown in the examples. I should ensure consistency between what appears in the file content and the filename itself, keeping the naming convention standardized across all recipe files. that pattern.\n\nLet me be systematic. I'll create all 10 files now:\n\n**File 1: Roasted Garlic and Herb Salmon.generated.21.txt** (OCR corruption)\n**File 2: Łazanki ze Śmietaną.generated.21.txt** (OCR corruption - Polish)\n**File 3: Beet and Walnut Salad.generated.21.txt** (OCR corruption)\n**File 4: Mushroom Crepe Appetizer.generated.21.txt** (OCR corruption)\n**File 5: Zupa z Dyni i Imbiru.generated.21.txt** (OCR corruption - Polish)\n**File 6: Apple Cinnamon Cake.generated.21.txt** (Narrative)\n**File 7: Piernik z Czarnuszką.generated.21.txt** (Narrative - Polish)\n**File 8: Baked Cod with Lemon.generated.21.txt** (Narrative)\n**File 9: Focaccia with Rosemary and Olives.generated.21.txt** (Compound)\n**File 10: Żurawina Kompot with Sugar.generated.21.txt** (Compound - Polish)\n\nI need to ensure the Polish filenames include proper diacritics—ł, ś, ź, and Ż—as specified in the requirements. This applies to the second, seventh, and tenth files.\n\nFor OCR files, I'll introduce realistic corruption patterns: digit substitutions (1 for l, 0 for O), dotless characters, hyphenation breaks, and garbled tokens. The narrative files need 3-7 lines of prose before the ingredient list, while compound files should contain multiple recipes within a single file. I need to rewrite the next thinking provided. Looking at the Polish recipe content, I'll rewrite it concisely while maintaining the original style and structure.\n\nCebulę pokroić w paski i usmażyć na maśle. Ugotowany makaron wymieszać z cebulą, następnie dodać śmietanę i dobrze połączyć. Doprawić solą i pieprzem do smaku, a całość podgrzewać przez kilka minut. Porcji wychodzi cztery. cup water\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n- 2 tbs butter, melted\n- 500 g mushrooms, sliced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 200 ml heavy cream\n- Thyme and parsley\n\nInstructions:\n1. Combine flour, eggs, milk, water, salt\n2. Melt butter in crepe pan\n3. Cook crepes 1-2 minutes per side\n4. Sauté mushrooms with garlic\n5. Add cream and herbs\n6. Fill crepes with mixture\n7. Roll and serve hot\n\nMakes 8-10 crepes\n\nZUPA Z DYNI I IMBIRU\n\nIngredients:\n- 1 kg pumpkin, cubed\n- 1.5 l vegetable broth\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 3 cm ginger, grated\n- Salt and pepper\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- Sour cream for serving\n\nPreparation:\n1. Melt butter in a pan\n2. Cook onion until soft\n3. Add ginger, stir for a moment\n4. Add pumpkin and broth\n5. Simmer 25-30 minutes until tender\n6. Blend or strain\n7. Stir in sour cream\n\nServes 4\n\n---\n\nAPPLE CINNAMON CAKE\n\nA wonderful autumn cake featuring the warm spice of cinnamon paired with roasted apples. The recipe carries family tradition, typically finished with powdered sugar and whipped cream. The tender texture and soft apple pieces make it a cherished dessert for gatherings.\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 tsp ground nutmeg\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n- 1/2 cup butter, softened\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 cup sour cream\n- 3 medium apples, peeled and diced\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nInstructions:\n1. Heat oven to 350°F\n2. Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt\n3. Cream butter with sugar until fluffy\n4. Add eggs individually while beating\n5. Alternate incorporating flour mixture and sour cream\n6. Gently mix in apples and vanilla\n7. Transfer to greased baking pan\n8. Bake 45-50 minutes until golden brown\n9. Let cool in pan before removing\n\nServes 8-10\n\n---\n\nPIERNIK Z CZARNUSZKĄ\n\nA traditional Polish spiced cake rich in aromatic seasonings and black seeds. The story goes that when grandmother made this, the kitchen would smell of spices for days afterward. Each generation adds their own touch, making it uniquely theirs. The black seeds bring a warm, aromatic depth that makes this cake unforgettable.\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 cups flour\n- 1/2 cup honey\n- 1/4 cup sugar\n- 4 eggs\n- 1 tsp black seeds\n- 2 tsp mixed spices\n- Pinch of salt\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n\nInstructions:\n1. Heat oven to 180°C\n2. Mix flour, black seeds, and spices together\n3. Beat eggs with sugar\n4. Fold in flour mixture\n5. Pour into cake pan\n6. Bake 35-40 minutes\n\nServes 8\n\nThe cod recipe continues with baking the fillets for 12-15 minutes until the flesh becomes opaque and flakes easily, then finishing with fresh lemon slices and parsley. The focaccia dough is prepared by combining flour, water, salt and yeast, kneading until it reaches a smooth, elastic texture, allowing it to rise for two hours, then pressing into an oiled pan and creating dimples across the surface with fingertips.\n\nFor the rosemary version, I add fresh rosemary sprigs and coarse sea salt before letting it rise another hour and baking at 450°F for 20-25 minutes. The olive focaccia follows a similar process but incorporates pitted olives distributed evenly across the dough, fresh oregano, and salt, with the same final rise and baking time. Both yield one focaccia each.\n\nThe cranberry compote recipe calls for simmering fresh cranberries with sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves, and lemon zest for 15 minutes, then cooling and jarring for storage. The preserved cranberry version uses a higher sugar ratio—1.5 kg sugar to 1 kg fresh berries with minimal water—and begins by washing the fruit before boiling. Sprawdzam długości plików — powinny mieć 15-60 linii. Większość moich przepisów mieści się w tym zakresie, z kilkoma plikami na granicy 40-60 linii. Przed utworzeniem plików muszę upewnić się, że żaden z przepisów nie pojawia się na liście wykluczonych pozycji, więc przeglądam je jeszcze raz pod kątem tych, które powinienem pominąć. Seared Scallops with Garlic, Mushroom and Barley Pilaf, Tomato Basil Pasta, Kompot Porzeczkowy, Kopytka z Pieczarkami, Bigos, Spiced Butternut Squash Soup, Piernik Czekoladowy, Pumpkin Pie with Spiced Cream, Mushroom Soup with Thyme, Lemon Cheesecake, Piernik z Orzechami, Herb Marinated Olives, Chocolate Mousse, Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli, Carrot Ginger Soup, Saffron Rice with Sausage, Blackberry Tart, Śledzie w Śmietanie, Grilled Squid with Garlic, Kompot Malinowy, Plac ki Ziemniaczane, Żurek, Barszcz Ukraiński, Kompot Czereśniowy, Naleśniki Słodkie z Dżemem, Zupa Koperkowa, Thai Green Curry, Pierniki Miodowe, Zupa Cebulowa, Lemon Blueberry Cake, Sałatka ze Świeżych Warzyw, Zupka Szczawiowa, Marinated Mushroom Salad, Kluski Śląskie z Grzybami, Żur z Ziemniaczkami, Lemon Custard Tart, Beef Tenderloin with Red Wine, Butternut Squash Pasta, Herb Crusted Lamb Chops, Crème Brûlée,\n\nTomato Basil Chicken, Mozzarella and Tomato Sandwich, Placki Rozankowe, Lentil Walnut Soup, Currant and Berry Compote, Elderberry Fool, Sernik, Chocolate Chip Brownies, Rogaliki Maślane, Kluski Śląskie z Mięsem, Crispy Eggplant, Leczo z Papryką\n\nChecking against my collection: Roasted Garlic and Herb Salmon, Łazanki ze Śmietaną, Beet and Walnut Salad, and Mushroom Crepe Appetizer are all absent from the compiled list. Zupa z Dyni still needs verification. Completing the sourdough recipe with basic instructions for both variations—mixing starter with flour and water, allowing rest time, incorporating seeds or herbs, bulk fermentation over several hours, shaping and overnight proofing, then scoring and baking at 450°F until done.\n\nNow verifying the full list against exclusions: the ten items avoid all the restricted recipes like Piernik Czekoladowy, Rosemary Focaccia, and Baked Eggs with Feta. The sourdough option with seeds and herbs replaces the earlier focaccia choice since that compound title doesn't match any excluded entries. Three files will contain OCR corruption markers as required by the pattern.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":66088,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":66088},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"540e7fab-35e2-47b9-ba67-9ffc9ac95c37","uuid":"99a00650-3686-49ca-a6ca-367e0c447401"}
