{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016N5dvSh6DmA3X1PEp28HNq","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Apple Cinnamon Cake.generated.21.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"540e7fab-35e2-47b9-ba67-9ffc9ac95c37","uuid":"f7f9a850-91f8-4b2d-b9bf-a4a6a264b890","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Apple Cinnamon Cake.generated.21.txt","content":"APPLE CINNAMON CAKE\n\nThis delightful apple cake is perfect for autumn gatherings and afternoon tea.\nThe aroma of cinnamon and roasted apples fills the kitchen while baking. This\nrecipe has been passed down through generations, traditionally served with a\ndusting of powdered sugar and a dollop of whipped cream. The moist crumb\nand tender apple pieces make this cake a beloved favorite at every gathering.\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- 2 tsp ground cinnamon\n- 1/2 tsp ground nutmeg\n- 1/4 tsp salt\n- 1/2 cup butter, softened\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 cup sour cream\n- 3 medium apples, peeled and diced\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 1/4 cup brown sugar for topping\n\nInstructions:\n1. Preheat oven to 350°F\n2. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt\n3. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy\n4. Beat in eggs one at a time\n5. Alternate adding flour mixture and sour cream\n6. Fold in apples and vanilla extract\n7. Pour into greased 9-inch pan\n8. Sprinkle brown sugar on top\n9. Bake 45-50 minutes until golden and toothpick comes out clean\n10. Cool in pan before turning out\n\nServes 8-10 people\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
