{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TBGhNBQ33rT2xYcvv32yzQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DzxJ7Wrnh5sXBAJEnskvaQ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Baked Cod with Lemon.generated.21.txt","content":"BAKED COD WITH LEMON\n\nCod is a delicate white fish that benefits from simple preparation and bright\nflavors. This recipe brings together the natural sweetness of fresh cod with\nthe brightness of fresh lemon and the earthiness of herbs. Perfect for a\nweeknight dinner, it comes together in less than thirty minutes and impresses\neven the most discerning palate. The gentle baking method preserves the fish's\ndelicate texture while infusing it with aromatic flavors.\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 cod fillets (6 oz each)\n- 3 fresh lemons\n- 4 tbsp olive oil\n- 4 sprigs fresh thyme\n- 2 cloves garlic, sliced thin\n- Sea salt and black pepper\n- 1/2 cup dry white wine\n- Fresh parsley for garnish\n- 1 tbsp capers (optional)\n\nInstructions:\n1. Preheat oven to 400°F\n2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper\n3. Arrange cod fillets on sheet\n4. Squeeze lemon juice over fish\n5. Drizzle with olive oil\n6. Add garlic slices and thyme\n7. Season with salt and pepper\n8. Pour wine around fillets\n9. Bake 12-15 minutes until fish flakes easily\n10. Garnish with lemon slices and parsley\n\nServes 4\nTotal time: 25 minutes\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":66088,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":66088},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"540e7fab-35e2-47b9-ba67-9ffc9ac95c37","uuid":"09d8c7e2-91bb-460e-80cd-48417507293d"}
